name: FIFO
info:
# FIFO
## First in First Out subflow
This flow receives a series of msg.payloads and builds a queue using FIFO (First in First out) method. The LIFO size is configurabe through subflow enviroment variables.

### Input
`msg.topic == put`
Will add the `msg.payload` to the end of the array. Everytime a new item is received the second output sends the complete queue.

`msg.topic == get`
Will remove the first item of the stack and will send it in the first output

`msg.topic == list`
Sends the complete list on the second output.

### Output 1
The first item on the top of the stack. It is sent only when `msg.topic == get`.

### Output 2
The complete queue in Array format. It is sent everytime a new item is added, removed or when `msg.topic == list`

### Status
Always show the queue size.

### Enviroment Variables
`Buffer_Size` defines the size of the queue. If a new item arrives and the queue is full, the oldest item will be removed.

name: Fingerprint Canvas
format:
<script>
    (function(scope) {
        scope.$watch('msg.payload', function(payload) {
            if(payload.image === undefined)
            {
                imageObj.src = defaultImage;
                minutia = [];
            }
            else
            {
                imageObj.src=payload.image.data;
                minutia = payload.minutia || [];
            }
        });
    }(scope));
    
    var minutia = [];
    var canvas = document.getElementById('myCanvas');
    var context = canvas.getContext('2d');
    context.fillStyle = "white";
    context.fillRect(0, 0, 280, 352);
    
    var imageObj = new Image(280, 352);
    
    imageObj.onload= function() {
        context.drawImage(imageObj, 0, 0);
        
        if(minutia.length > 0)
        {
            context.lineWidth = 2;
            context.strokeStyle = "#FF0000";
            minutia.forEach(function(element){
                if(element.type === 1)
                    context.strokeStyle = "#FF0000";
                else
                    context.strokeStyle = "#0000FF";
                context.beginPath();
                context.arc(element.x, element.y, 15, 0, 2 * Math.PI);
                context.stroke();
            });
        }
    };
    let defaultImage = "data:image/jpeg;base64,"
    imageObj.src = defaultImage;
    
</script>
